<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1566,2023]" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,434,1782,1807]" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">Species description.</emphasis>
Prosome ovoid in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[803,875,1783,1807]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,249,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[215,1377,342,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[206,1381,339,1927]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pertsovius tridentatus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype female. 1 — antennule, 2 — habitus, dorsal; 3 — habitus, from the left side; 4 — urosome, ventral; 5 — genital double somite, left side; 6 — antenna; 7 — mandibular palp; 8 — mandibular blade, 9 — maxillule, 10 — maxilla, 11 — maxilliped. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208019/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">
Fig. 
<number box="[858,875,1783,1807]" pageId="7" pageNumber="40" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
: 
<number box="[889,905,1783,1807]" pageId="7" pageNumber="40" value="2.0">2</number>
), nearly 
<number box="[1007,1042,1783,1807]" pageId="7" pageNumber="40" value="2.9">2.9</number>
times as long as urosome and 
<number box="[1401,1436,1783,1807]" pageId="7" pageNumber="40" value="2.1">2.1</number>
times as long as wide. The first pediger separate from cephalosome, pedigers four and five fused.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1566,2023]" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">
Genital double somite almost symmetrical ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[818,892,1855,1879]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,249,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[215,1377,342,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[206,1381,339,1927]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pertsovius tridentatus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype female. 1 — antennule, 2 — habitus, dorsal; 3 — habitus, from the left side; 4 — urosome, ventral; 5 — genital double somite, left side; 6 — antenna; 7 — mandibular palp; 8 — mandibular blade, 9 — maxillule, 10 — maxilla, 11 — maxilliped. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208019/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">
Fig. 
<number box="[875,892,1855,1879]" pageId="7" pageNumber="40" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
: 
<number box="[907,923,1855,1879]" pageId="7" pageNumber="40" value="4.0">4</number>
), slightly expanding laterally approximately equal in length to two following somites combined. Anterior part of genital double somite protruding ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[159,230,1927,1951]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,249,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[215,1377,342,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[206,1381,339,1927]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pertsovius tridentatus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype female. 1 — antennule, 2 — habitus, dorsal; 3 — habitus, from the left side; 4 — urosome, ventral; 5 — genital double somite, left side; 6 — antenna; 7 — mandibular palp; 8 — mandibular blade, 9 — maxillule, 10 — maxilla, 11 — maxilliped. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208019/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">
Fig. 
<number box="[213,230,1927,1951]" pageId="7" pageNumber="40" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
: 
<number box="[244,260,1927,1951]" pageId="7" pageNumber="40" value="5.0">5</number>
). Spermathecae visible in ventral view but not obvious when viewed laterally. Anal somite nearly two times longer than preceding somite. Caudal rami slightly asymmetrical, with left ramus slightly longer than right, both bearing four setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,536]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41">
Antennule of 
<number box="[353,381,151,175]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" value="24.0">24</number>
free segments not reaching anal somite (
<figureCitation box="[849,919,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,249,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[215,1377,342,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[206,1381,339,1927]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pertsovius tridentatus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype female. 1 — antennule, 2 — habitus, dorsal; 3 — habitus, from the left side; 4 — urosome, ventral; 5 — genital double somite, left side; 6 — antenna; 7 — mandibular palp; 8 — mandibular blade, 9 — maxillule, 10 — maxilla, 11 — maxilliped. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208019/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number box="[902,919,151,175]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
: 
<number box="[932,948,151,175]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" value="3.0">3</number>
). Mouthparts (
<figureCitation box="[1117,1187,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,249,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[215,1377,342,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[206,1381,339,1927]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pertsovius tridentatus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype female. 1 — antennule, 2 — habitus, dorsal; 3 — habitus, from the left side; 4 — urosome, ventral; 5 — genital double somite, left side; 6 — antenna; 7 — mandibular palp; 8 — mandibular blade, 9 — maxillule, 10 — maxilla, 11 — maxilliped. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208019/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number box="[1170,1187,151,175]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
: 
<number box="[1200,1257,151,175]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" value="8.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="6.0">6–10</number>
) relatively well developed compared with other discoid genera, and of typical structure for genus. Maxilliped (
<figureCitation box="[1218,1288,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,249,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[215,1377,342,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[206,1381,339,1927]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pertsovius tridentatus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype female. 1 — antennule, 2 — habitus, dorsal; 3 — habitus, from the left side; 4 — urosome, ventral; 5 — genital double somite, left side; 6 — antenna; 7 — mandibular palp; 8 — mandibular blade, 9 — maxillule, 10 — maxilla, 11 — maxilliped. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208019/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number box="[1271,1288,188,212]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
: 
<number box="[1300,1327,188,212]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" value="11.0">11</number>
) syncoxa with no setae on lobe one.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,536]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41">
Р 
<number box="[212,224,260,284]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" value="1.0">1</number>
-Р 
<number box="[251,265,260,284]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" value="4.0">4</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[283,366,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,249,1319,1342]" captionTargetBox="[210,1374,202,1280]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[200,1386,193,1298]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pertsovius tridentatus gen. et sp. nov. Female (1 – 2 and 4 – 5 — holotype, 3 — paratype). 1 — Р 1; 2 — exopod of P 2; 3 — Р 2; 4 — Р 3; 5 — Р 4. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208020/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="41">
Figs. 
<number box="[348,366,260,284]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
: 
<number box="[379,421,260,284]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" value="3.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="1.0">1–5</number>
) of typical structure for genus: endopods one-segmented, and exopods three-segmented. Outer spine on first segment of P 
<number box="[531,541,295,319]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" value="1.0">1</number>
exopod relatively long, but not reaching middle of third segment. Outer spines of second and third segments of exopod approximately equal in length, and almost two times shorter than outer spine on first segment. Outer spine on first exopodal segment of Р 
<number box="[928,942,367,391]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" value="2.0">2</number>
reaching distal border of second segment. Outer edge of third segment of P 
<number box="[518,532,404,428]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" value="2.0">2</number>
exopod with three external spines on both legs in 
<typeStatus box="[1095,1193,404,428]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus box="[1247,1347,405,429]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41">paratype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,536]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,460,439,464]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
In the presence of three external spines on third segment of Р 
<number box="[1160,1176,439,463]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" value="2.0">2</number>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1188,1338,440,464]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Discoidae" genus="Pertsovius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Calanoida" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1188,1338,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="41">P. tridentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1346,1436,440,464]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1346,1436,440,464]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from all other species of this genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,1389,511,536]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,536]" box="[197,1389,511,536]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,332,512,536]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the number of external spines on the distal segment of P 
<number box="[1279,1293,511,535]" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" value="2.0">2</number>
exopod.
</paragraph>
